      "outcome": "The Wardens pull back from the canal approach, ending their contested chokepoint on gondola traffic. The Signal-House Families immediately celebrate the withdrawal as a victory, and their \"doubly authenticated\" message-courier service flows freely through the Lantern-Lit Gondola Pier for the first time in weeks. However, the Wardens' garrison is no longer stretched thin — Tower Bridge Concourse is now heavily fortified with the full complement of polearm guards and crossbowmen. More importantly, the Wardens' informant network begins compiling a dossier on the Lacquer Authority's suspicious archive access. Several informants report that Authority artificers were seen copying seal templates far beyond what the Council's \"supervised access\" permit allowed — and that at least one artificer was observed sketching the layout of the archive's inner vault. The Wardens now possess a potential weapon: evidence that the Lacquer Authority exploited the Council's trust to conduct espionage inside the Seal Verification Chamber.",
