      "outcome": "The Warden garrison pulls back from the canal approach under cover of night, abandoning their secondary chokepoint. The Signal-House Families immediately reclaim unimpeded access to the Lantern-Lit Gondola Pier, and their \"doubly authenticated\" gondola traffic surges. However, the Wardens' consolidation strengthens their defensive position at Tower Bridge Concourse — the garrison is no longer stretched thin, and the checkpoint's fortifications are reinforced with additional crossbow positions. The Warden envoy arrives at the Shrine Auditors' Council with a formal arbitration demand, citing seventeen procedural irregularities in the annulment decree. The Council, already distracted by their Silent Spire consecration efforts, agrees to hear the case — buying the Wardens time. Meanwhile, the Wardens' informants begin circulating pamphlets questioning the legitimacy of the Families' consecrated charter, sowing doubt among superstitious operators. The Wardens have lost ground but preserved their core position — for now.",
